Encapsulation:
it is on eof the 4 fundamental OOP concepts.
It create classes to write code and store date, use private access
modifiers to secure the data by limiting the access, create getter setter
methods for every field if you want others to change or see those
fields.
Why should we learn about Encapsulations?
It improves the control over the data that we store in the fields
of a class which leads us to more secure code.
